chapter 1-5
Good reason to have clean code:
1.	Save time to find bugs
2.	Save time to maintain the code
3.	Easy to test
4.	Look beautiful 
Naming:
1.	Use Nouns for Variables, Properties, Parameters
2.	Use Verbs for Methods and Functions
3.	Pronounceable and Unambiguous
Comments:
1.	Not reliable, since it not updated with code
2.	Cannot make bad code look good 
3.	Not need for record, since we use version control 
4.	Remove unused code, don’t comment out it 
Function:
1.	Keep it short
2.	Easy to test
3.	Easy to expend
Reason to prevent clean code:
I’ll clean it up later
